d = OrderedDict([('a', 1), ('b', ''), ('c', []), ('d', [1, 2])])
d['meta'] = OrderedDict([('a', 1), ('b', ''), ('c', {}), ('d', [1, 2])])
d['documents'] = {(1): OrderedDict([('a', 1), ('b', ''), ('c', []), ('d', [
    1, 2])]), (2): OrderedDict([('a', 1), ('b', ''), ('c', {}), ('d', [1, 2])])
    }
actual = pyjsonnlp.remove_empty_fields(d)
expected = OrderedDict([('a', 1), ('d', [1, 2]), ('meta', OrderedDict([('a',
    1), ('d', [1, 2])])), ('documents', {(1): OrderedDict([('a', 1), ('d',
    [1, 2])]), (2): OrderedDict([('a', 1), ('d', [1, 2])])})])
assert expected == actual, actual
